File: South Africa's Eben Etzebeth in action. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Human Rights Commission is instituting legal proceedings against Springbok lock Eben Etzebeth in the Equality Court on Friday. This relates to a complaint received by the Commission in August, in which Etzebeth is accused of physical assault and racial abuse, during an altercation in Langebaan. READ: Peter de Villiers won't support Boks at World Cup He has denied the allegations. READ: SAHRC takes on Malema over Mugabe tweets The French-based lock is currently on duty at the 2019 Rugby World Cup in Japan with the Springboks. 